article.headline: W. Illinois 66, Kennesaw State 54
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Sophomore David Nurse scored a game-high 18 points, including four 3-pointers, to lead Western Illinois in a 66-54 victory over Kennesaw State Saturday afternoon. David Jackson added 16 points, Jerryck Owens-Murray had 13 and David DuBois chipped in 10 for the Leathernecks (4-7). Owens-Murray had 10 rebounds and four assists for Western Illinois, which led 40-25 at the half. The Leathernecks shot 38-for-60 from the field, or about 63 percent. That compared with 29-for-67, or about 43 percent, for the Owls (2-8). Shuan Stegall scored 14 points, Ronell Wooten had 11 and Jon-Michael Nickerson added 10 for the Owls. Wooten had six rebounds and three 3-pointers for Kennesaw State.
